Description: Rim and neck sherd of Milesian Fikellura pottery jug with flaring rim and handle root on left; very worn; probable white slip on exterior; interior glazed save lowest part preserved; exterior: wide band below rim; part of double cable band, as frequent on the shape.
Curator's comments: For parallels, see CVA, Rodi, Museo Archeologico Dello Spedale Dei Cavalieri 1, II.D.L.4, Pl.5, no.3.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GF.077)
